channel.title: Need help portforwarding! useing action tec router and verison!
channel.description: i am trying to make and server. im at the port forwarding part. acourding to the tut, mine looks nothign like this! can someonehelp me? or tell me what to do? here is and pic in the ip portforwarding section in my router. http://s945.photobucket.com/albums/ad298/reddead228/?action=view&current=help1.jpg

item.title: Need help portforwarding! useing action tec router and verison!
item.dc:creator: @noobofiyer noobofiyer
item.description:
@noobofiyer wrote:

[quote=“Hidendra, post:4, topic:287299”][quote author=noobofiyer link=topic=379893.msg2856309#msg2856309 date=1246891058]

pick device.
protocol: leavy empty
wan connection type: tcp (if that’s there…?)
forward to port: 43594 (if your server uses 43594, it’s default)
when: Always (?)

U rite. i use same router. aswelll.

And ill got a server,
[/quote]
I use a Belkin :P, I inferred what would be in the other fields.[/quote]
